{"id": 48, "ts": 1778840132.569974, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 2, "agent": "agent_3", "message": "We now have an additional piece of information: Candidate\u202fC \u201chandles stress very well,\u201d confirming that they are calm under pressure. This adds a valuable strength to C\u2019s profile, which already includes quick, correct decision\u2011making, excellent attention skills, and a genuine concern for others\u2014attributes that support teamwork and sound judgment on long\u2011haul flights.\nHowever, we still lack any explicit evidence of Candidate\u202fC\u2019s reliability, which is a non\u2011negotiable safety requirement for international, high\u2011responsibility operations. In contrast, Candidate\u202fB is the only candidate with a clear statement of **100\u202f% reliability** and **calmness in a crisis**, directly satisfying the two most critical criteria. B also brings solid technical competence (weather assessment and computer skills) essential for long\u2011distance navigation and planning. While B\u2019s interpersonal drawbacks (being perceived as pretentious and occasionally using the wrong tone) could affect crew dynamics, these issues are secondary to the proven safety\u2011critical attributes of reliability and composure.\nGiven the current evidence\u2014reliability and calmness confirmed for B, calmness but no reliability for C, and only partial or uncertain evidence for A and D\u2014Candidate\u202fB remains the strongest overall fit for the long\u2011distance pilot role.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_3\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}"}
